aa(lp76
VNow social scientists call this the paradox of aging.
p77
aVI mean, after all, aging is not a piece of cake.
p78
aVSo we've asked all sorts of questions to see if we could undo this finding.
p79
aVWe've asked whether it may be that the current generations of older people
p80
aVare and always have been the greatest generations.
p81
aVThat is that younger people today may not typically experience
p82
aVthese improvements as they grow older.
p83
aVWe've asked,
p84
aVwell, maybe older people are just trying to put a positive spin
p85
